                  Since this post seems to have gone a little downhill into class wars, I would like to toss a little bit of gas on the fire.<br />
<br />
Since necros and sorcs are hate capped in raids(although necros pets can do damage without counting twards their hate.) a class comparison really does have to take into account soloing ability. Otherwise it really is about how much utility a caster can add above DPS.<br />
<br />
As for psions we are not utility/DPS, I would put us more at utility/CC. Then with limited things that are mezable and limited things that can be petted all we become good for is buffs. As stated before a psion can pull agro off a tank just like any other caster, but we have to use our self depreciating abilities to do so, and as opposed to a sorc we do not get equitable returns for our trouble. <br />
<br />
So in conclusion, what's a psion's role? Nobody knows. Why is everyone creating a necro? Because they still have the same DPS cap in raid, but you can solo your way to 50 quickly. <br />
<br />
As for the content being the problem not the class, damn straight. A 5 dot mob that is imune to mez and charm should not be frearable. Same is true with a non creature class mob. But right now there are mobs I can't pet, but my wife can fear them all day long. Add that to the ability to life tap mobs, a permanent pet, and FD. So yes, the content needs to be fixed, but so does the class, otherwise might as well fill every raid caster role with necros (because they can keep themselves healed) and then just use the other classes for group 4.<br />
<br />
Sorry Druids, dunno what to tell you. <img src="images/smilies/frown.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Frown" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
Edit: Oh and for the record, before it comes up: Psion pets do less damage than necro pets when the necro pet is well augmented. Also ours can't be sacrificed for health, and they have this nasty habit of turning on us at bad times and killing us. Oh and if they have the augmentation which give the abomination health for damage dealt they can tank 3 dot mobs themselves. Sorry, but this doesn't seem even remotely balanced.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
