		<div id="post_message_1285877">
                  
                  I will hold my tounge on psionicists until we hear more about what the devs plan on actually &quot;doing.&quot;<br />
<br />
Considering they will be dealing damage under rogues but higher than monks and rangers, i dont think they will be &quot;bad&quot; at dps at all in a raid, but rather that they will indeed be more &quot;bard like&quot; in that they add more dps &quot;though&quot; their allies by vastly improving caster dps and possibly lowering their hate be REALLY large amounts to enable them to &quot;deal&quot; this higher damage with less risk.<br />
<br />
If psionicists have access to this kind of potiental, and its kept &quot;same group only,&quot; then they will be just as adventageous as a bard on raids when it comes to be a dps nessessity almost for casters, and hopefully bard's buffs are changed to only effect melee classes for the most part.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
That is the BIGGEST flaw that i've noticed with buffing, are the + damage buffs.<br />
<br />
They are all damage.<br />
<br />
Not melee specific, not ranged specific, not spell specific.<br />
<br />
<br />
I see no reason why a cleric's Strength of the Gods should effect spell damage in any way, nor a bard song that is essentially rallying the strength of your comrads in combat (note, im not talking about the obvious caster-themed componants, but the &quot;war song&quot; type componants)<br />
<br />
I see no reason why a &quot;jolt&quot; symbiote should effect casters, how is this little angery attatchment going to make you strike twice with your spells?<br />
<br />
<br />
A cleric should not be a good addition to a caster dps group, their buffs should not be hugely beneficial for that.<br />
<br />
A bloodmage SHOULD be a good addition to a caster dps group, and their buffs should be geared towards such.<br />
<br />
<br />
If buffs are ever moved to a most restricted rout, such as same group only, then they all need serious review, and damage modification buffs especially need to only effect the damage than makes since.<br />
<br />
A war cry/song/frenzy should not effect spell damage, just as spell damage boosting abilities should not effect melee damage.<br />
<br />
I think this could really even up the buffing-capability of many classes if they introduce new buffs to classes that currently are lack luster in that area (only when it make since though) by diverging the general &quot;damage&quot; buffs.<br />
<br />
Psionicists, Bloodmages, Phoenix shamans and Dreadknights would obviously be the prime canidates for Spell damage enhancement, while Disciples, Clerics (more so in war clerics), Bear shamans, Bards and Warriors would be the prime canidates for Melee damage enhancement.<br />
<br />
Bards should be the strongest enhancer for melee, with Psionicist's being the strongest enhancer for spells, while each is mildly acceptable at the other role. (some melee haste for psions, some energy cost reductions ect for bards so they can still help the opposite damage types out a bit)<br />
<br />
The rest can just fall in how the devs see fit, the general rule being the more damage you do personally, the less you buff up in your group.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
And there is my hypothetical conversation tome of the evening, time to waste 2 hours of my life reading a 1900's Humanities novel <i>Thus Spoke Zarathustra </i>....
                  
