		<div id="post_message_1287151">
                  
                  Alright, have to come in and step on the caster's toes.  Jades actually asked me here to discuss a rogue's view here.  Kardolmer is the class lead, but he's a slacker.<br />
<br />
Anyway, here's what I see.  Sorcs and Rogues should be top DPS. Period.  All we do is DPS.  We bring nothing else to raiding.  Ruin (our debuff) is -14% damage, and -16% accuracy.  It apparently is stacking when it shouldn't, so... don't count on it.<br />
<br />
Sorcs should have a HUGE burst DPS advantage over us, and we should have the long haul DPS.  You guys have the range advantage, and we eat the AEs.  Talking to Jades, apparently you eat AEs too, which should change.  Give you longer range (hell, all casters) to avoid the AE.<br />
<br />
My current reason I out DPS you guys is due to hate management.  You need SOMETHING to help you out, cuz right now you have nothing.  It's useless and broken.  But, high DPS should equal high risk.  My risk right now is too low, and yours is too high.  Monks with FD have even less risk, heh.  Something should be done to address all these issues.<br />
<br />
I don't think a druid should out DPS me, and unless it's a SUPER long fight, a necro shouldn't either.<br />
<br />
So, nutshell:  Sorcs shouldn't be higher than rogues.  Right now, you ARE, but you have no hate management.  Doh.  It needs to equal out in the end.  I don't think you should be at 4000, and us at 3500 - higher risk = higher reward (DPS).  This should be balanced, without anyone being nerfed.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
