                  As I said, you shouldn't be hit by AE.  That's kinda the point.  You are a ranged class, your benefit is avoiding stuff like that.  That's why you have less HP, less AC, etc.  I agree 100% on that.<br />
<br />
The crit feedback on CV is part of the risk to equal your DPS.  It shouldn't be in addition to AEs, etc.<br />
<br />
You honestly think that a 4% crit increase for the raid is THAT high?  I mean, seriously.  DKs give what, 15%?  We get that ability at level 10.  It's not gamebreaking by any stretch.  Yes, it's a new ability, but it starts at 4%, and stays at 4%.  If we count &quot;added DPS&quot; as a basis of class DPS, then bards are blowing away EVERY class EVER.  My DPS is as high as it is BECAUSE of a bard.<br />
<br />
And as I said, I have no issue with you doing 4000 DPS to my 3500 DPS.  If your risk matches mine, then boom, go for it.  I disagree with the concept behind it - caster &gt; melee is a bad concept, there should be equality.  I have a few more HP because I eat AEs.  You should be out of their range, and that is where the equality lies.  We should be similar in DPS.
                  
