	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_1287379">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1287379">
                  
                  I've never asked for any class in VG to be nerfed, and I find focusing on the 'grass is greener' approach to be counter productive, but I do know that the risk of most caster classes is higher than the risk of most melee classes in end game currently, and yet the DPS potential seems to almost be the inverse.<br />
<br />
Casters do eat AE's, have less hps than melee and often burn hp to do there best dps, as either direct damage or canibalising health for energy.<br />
To compound this, in most raid fights 100 caster damage = ~ 80 hate at max range where 100 melee dps = ~65 hate at 3m...<br />
<br />
The problem imo lies in two primary issues.<br />
1) Agro management - We've talked about it at large, and simply casters lack the ability to manage there agro and keep up dps at the same way that melee can. Reasons for this are both Melee getting multiple % based hate reduction abilities where casters get static hate reduction AND Melee getting more/stronger hate reduction options than casters.<br />
<br />
2) Buff Stacking - Damage buffs generaly stack better with melee than with casters. Casting time of spells should mean fewer but bigger hits, however +damage buffs for melee affect pasive 'auto-attack' as well as special instant abilities. This means that melee get more damage from a static damage buff like those of bards which add +# damage rather than +% damage. <br />
<br />
Its pretty simple math, and could be easily ballanced if +melee damage and + spell damage buffs were seperated, but there not and because of this these a +100 damage buff can mean a difference of +100 * 2 autoattacks *1.5 per 3 sec + 100 * 2 per 3 sec for 2 special attacks VS +100 for 1 spell per 3 sec... in that example its a 5:1 damage ratio in favor of melee on # damage buffs.<br />
<br />
Both of these issues are due to an oversight in the use of static vs scaled abilities and could be avoided by re-desiging the abilities with a more wholistic view of the &quot;DPS meta-archetype&quot; (meaning both melee and ranged)<br />
<br />
I just hope they 'get it' sooner rather than later, because right now I'm quite over VG. We have way over-worked devs and no real commitment by SoE to get the game where it should be. There too busy trying to make the newbie experience good and fixing end game is not a real priority as a consequence. Its unlikely this imo 'huge imbalance' will be resolved before July... given that Psi re-vamp isn't even included in end Feb GU4 acording to January Producers letter, Heck I will be plesantly shocked if they finaly get this sorted out by GU8... which would make it about in time for next christmas, maybe by then I will decide to play again. /sigh
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
